Initiate the necessary administrative and/or criminal action in case of unjustified failure/refusal to effect compliance with the foregoing requirements by subordinate officials.

Optimize the utilization of the 20 percent LDF and implement the PAPs within the timelines in order to achieve the socio-economic and environmental outcomes, essential in the attainment of its goals and objectives of a desired quality of life for its constituents;

Consider the equitable distribution on PAPs  listed among the three important aspects of Sector development mandated under DILG/DBM JMC No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017  and previous issuances as well as the requirements of Sections 16 and 17 of the LGC of 1991, in order to cater not only to the infrastructure needs of the constituents but also on environment, agriculture, fishery and livelihood programs, projects and activities which will directly address the actual needs of the intended beneficiaries; and

Adopt well-defined strategies in order to enhance the present monitoring and review activities during the planning, procurement, contract implementation and program evaluation phase, in order for the planners, implementers as well as evaluators to continuously monitor the timely implementation, so that immediate appropriate and corrective actions could be done on noted gaps along the way.

Submit to the Audit Team the RDS related to the purchase of the 300 bags of NFA rice or a valid justification why the dates of the distribution comes ahead of the date of purchase;

Submit the Program Profile for the implementation of the rice program to indigent families to support the validity of the procurement and for proper monitoring and evaluation;

Account for the difference of 23 bags of rice for procurements made for CY 2016; and

